# 🎨 Image Smoothing Filter UI

A simple **client-side image smoothing filter tool** built with **pure HTML, CSS, and JavaScript** using the **Canvas API**.

![HTML5](https://img.shields.io/badge/HTML5-E34F26?style=flat-square&logo=html5&logoColor=white)
![CSS3](https://img.shields.io/badge/CSS3-1572B6?style=flat-square&logo=css3&logoColor=white)
![JavaScript](https://img.shields.io/badge/JavaScript-F7DF1E?style=flat-square&logo=javascript&logoColor=black)

## ✨ Features

- **📁 Image Upload** - Upload any image from your device
- **🖼️ Original Display** - View the original image rendered on canvas
- **⚫ Grayscale Option** - Convert to grayscale before smoothing
- **🔧 Kernel Size** - Choose between 3×3 or 5×5 smoothing kernels
- **✨ Smooth Filter** - Apply neighborhood averaging blur effect
- **🎯 Pixel Inspector** - Hover to view real-time RGBA values

## 🚀 Quick Start

1. **Clone the repository**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/image-smoothing-filter.git
   cd image-smoothing-filter
   ```

2. **Open in browser**
   ```bash
   open index.html
   ```

That's it! No build tools or server needed — runs entirely in the browser.

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Technology | Purpose |
|------------|---------|
| **HTML5** | Structure & Canvas element |
| **Vanilla JS** | Core image processing logic |
| **Canvas API** | Pixel manipulation & rendering |
| **CSS3** | Modern styling & layout |

## 🔬 How It Works

### Image Processing Pipeline
1. **Upload** → Uses `FileReader` API to load image data
2. **Display** → Renders original image on canvas using `drawImage()`
3. **Process** → Extracts pixel data with `getImageData()`
4. **Filter** → Applies neighborhood averaging algorithm
5. **Output** → Renders smoothed result to second canvas

### Smoothing Algorithm
```javascript
// Simplified smoothing logic
for (each pixel) {
    newValue = average(neighboringPixels);
    outputPixel = newValue;
}
```

